page.title: 09FLEETWOOD PARK
page.content: Memorial Park provides a lot of entertainment and happiness for young and old people. There are tennis courts, and for the elderly people there is a bowling green. There are lots of flowers and near the duck pond are many trees. People go to sit in the rose garden and many go to the park to feed the ducks and to enjoy seeing them waddling about. Toddlers go to the park to play on the swings or to see the ducks. There are 10 big swings, 5 small "high-chair" swings, a monkey-frame, 3 slides of different heights and a spider's web roundabout. It is a pity that the youths vandalize the swings and slides. In the middle of the park is a monument naming the people who died in the 2nd World War and on Remembrance Day the park is always full of people. The gardens and flowers are looked after very well.
